    "description": "<p>Red-shelled insects that look like a cross between an ant and a beetle, but the size of a small cat. They form colonies a few-hundred large, typically on higher ground, harvesting all the dead grass in a few miles, hibernating through winter, then relocating in spring to a part of the Flats that hasn't burned or been harvested in years. They mostly ignore people and large animals, but they'll swarm if threatened.</p>",
